    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I make a packing list for a trip?</h3>
        <p>Start by selecting your destination type (beach, city, mountain, or cold weather), trip duration, and travel style. Then organize items by category: clothing, toiletries, electronics, documents, health supplies, and miscellaneous. Use a packing checklist generator to ensure you don't forget essentials, and check off items as you pack them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What are the essentials to pack for any trip?</h3>
        <p>Every packing list should include: passport or ID, travel insurance documents, phone and charger, basic toiletries, medications, comfortable walking shoes, weather-appropriate clothing layers, a reusable water bottle, and copies of important documents. These essentials remain the same regardless of your destination.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How many outfits should I pack for a week-long trip?</h3>
        <p>For a 7-day trip, pack 4-5 tops, 2-3 bottoms, 7 sets of underwear and socks, 1-2 pairs of shoes, and 1 jacket or layering piece. Choose versatile items that mix and match. Backpackers can pack fewer items and plan to do laundry, while checked-luggage travelers can bring more variety.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What should I pack for a beach vacation?</h3>
        <p>Beach vacation essentials include: swimsuits (2-3), reef-safe sunscreen (SPF 50+), sunglasses, a wide-brim hat, lightweight cover-ups, sandals and water shoes, a beach towel or sarong, aloe vera gel, a dry bag for electronics, and light breathable clothing. Don't forget insect repellent and a reusable water bottle.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I pack light for a carry-on only trip?</h3>
        <p>To pack carry-on only: use packing cubes, roll clothes instead of folding, choose a neutral color palette so everything mixes and matches, wear your bulkiest items on the plane, use solid toiletries under 100ml, limit shoes to 2 pairs, and choose quick-dry fabrics. A 40L backpack or standard carry-on suitcase can hold enough for 1-2 weeks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What should I not forget to pack?</h3>
        <p>The most commonly forgotten travel items are: phone charger and adapter, medications and prescriptions, travel insurance documents, sunscreen, a reusable water bottle, a rain jacket, copies of important documents, ear plugs and eye mask, a small first aid kit, and snacks for the journey. Use a packing checklist to avoid forgetting these essentials.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do I pack for cold weather travel?</h3>
        <p>For cold weather destinations, pack in layers: thermal base layers, insulating mid-layers (fleece or down), and a waterproof outer shell. Bring warm accessories like a beanie, gloves, and a scarf. Pack wool socks, insulated waterproof boots, and hand warmers. Use compression bags to save space with bulky winter clothing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I save my packing list progress?</h3>
        <p>Yes, this packing list generator automatically saves your checked items and custom additions to your browser's localStorage. Your progress persists between sessions so you can come back and continue packing. You can also print your checklist for offline use or reset your list to start fresh.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related pages -->
    <section>
